******
[1] Omsk Oblast
Date: Thu 24 June 2010
From: Infomsk.Ru [translated by ATS, edited]
<http://www.infomsk.ru/news/2010/06/24/v_omske_zafiksirovanyi_pervyie_sluchai_zarajeniya_kleschevyim_entsefalitom/>


Cases of tick-borne encephalitis recorded in Omsk Oblast
--------------------------------------------------------
The 1st cases of tick-borne encephalitis (TBE) in 2010 have been
registered in Omsk. A diagnosis of TBE virus infection was confirmed
in 3 patients, 2 from Omsk and 1 from Tari. There was also one
confirmed case of tick-borne borelliosis this year in Omsk.

So far this year a total of 3264 people have sought medical attention
as a consequence of tick-bites. Of these 903 were children. 304 cases
of tick-bite were recorded in the city of Omsk, and the rest in rural
districts.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail-RUS
